from datetime import datetime
print("Code Start:",datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'))
def date_price(s):
    json_acceptable_string = s.replace("'", "\"")
    d = json.loads(json_acceptable_string)
    df=pd.DataFrame(d.items())
    df.columns=['metric','values']
    df=df[df['metric'].isin(['date','close'])]
    return df['values'].tolist()
    
test1['new']=test1.apply(lambda x:date_price(x['historical']),axis=1)
test1['new']=test1['new'].astype('str')
test1['new'] = test1['new'].str.replace("'", "")
test1['new'] = test1['new'].str.replace("'", "")
test1['new'] = test1['new'].str.strip('[]')
test1[['date','price']] = test1['new'].str.split(',',expand=True)
test1=test1[['symbol','date','price']]
print("Code End:",datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'))

# Create random data with numpy
import numpy as np
np.random.seed(1)

N = 100
random_x = np.linspace(0, 1, N)
random_y0 = np.random.randn(N) + 5
random_y1 = np.random.randn(N)
random_y2 = np.random.randn(N) - 5

fig = go.Figure()

# Add traces
fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=random_x, y=random_y0,
                    mode='markers',
                    name='markers'))
fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=random_x, y=random_y1,
                    mode='lines+markers',
                    name='lines+markers'))
fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=random_x, y=random_y2,
                    mode='lines',
                    name='lines'))

    x = r.json()

    data2=df
    data2['text']=data2['text'].str.lower()

    newStopWords = ['market', "2020", "stock", 'stocks','share','shares', 'nyse','nasdaq','said','nyse','airline','airlines']
    stopwords.update(newStopWords)

    data2['text']=data2['text'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join([word for word in x.split() if word not in (stopwords)]))
    from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer

    corpus = data2['text'].tolist()

    vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(stop_words='english')
    vecs = vectorizer.fit_transform(corpus)
    feature_names = vectorizer.get_feature_names()
    dense = vecs.todense()
    lst1 = dense.tolist()
    df2 = pd.DataFrame(lst1, columns=feature_names)
    x = vectorizer.vocabulary_
    wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color="white", max_words=50).generate_from_frequencies(df2.T.sum(axis=1))
    # i='NFLX.jpg'
    # wordcloud.to_image(i)
    fig = plt.figure(figsize = (12,14))
    #company=sample[sample['symbol']==i]['Company'].values.tolist()[0]
    plt.title(i+':News Wordcloud',fontsize = 25, weight = 'bold')

import requests
page = requests.get("https://www.marketbeat.com/earnings/conference-calls/")
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
from requests import get
from csv import writer

url = 'https://www.marketbeat.com/earnings/conference-calls/'

r = get(url)
soup = BeautifulSoup(r.text, 'lxml')


# get all tables
tables = soup.find_all('table')

# loop over each table
for num, table in enumerate(tables, start=1):

    # create filename
    filename = 'table-%d.csv' % num

    # open file for writing
    with open(filename, 'w') as f:

        # store rows here
        data = []

        # create csv writer object
        csv_writer = writer(f)

        # go through each row
        rows = table.find_all('tr')
        for row in rows:

            # write headers if any
            headers = row.find_all('th')
            if headers:
                csv_writer.writerow([header.text.strip() for header in headers])

            # write column items
            columns = row.find_all('td')
            csv_writer.writerow([column.text.strip() for column in columns])
